{
  "stem": "26609.18",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can see his face.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the director, kind of director there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I came up to him, not knowing his name and said, could you help me?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I want to go back to my name, but they spoke, Hungarian people spoke all Yiddish because they were more religious people, and no one would understand his Hungarian of the other countries' survivors.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they spoke Yiddish between themselves.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I came up and I had said-- I couldn't speak Polish to him, because he couldn't understand-- though I thought I speak Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my Yiddish, so many years in Germany, was not Yiddish, it was German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't realize how, how I spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was German.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I came up and, and said, I said-- now I know, because later, I learned Yiddish from them-- now I know that I would have to say, [NON-ENGLISH] but I said [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] So I said, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I said, again.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He said to another one, the [NON-ENGLISH] to Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I tell you later why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] Let her go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He wanted to throw me out, and I said, what?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans did it to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now the Jews are doing it to me?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Germans didn't want me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now Jews don't want me?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Why don't you speak Yiddish?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, I do speak Yiddish [? to ?] [? you. ?] But it was German.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was Germanized.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he said, oh, because it happened before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "After the war, it's very well-known, in Israel that a number of German girls-- who knows who they were-- and even, even some wives of the Gestapo, or they killed themselves in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But our boys, the Jewish boys, didn't have enough girls, because there were, was a-- a shortage of Jewish women.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
